sql:
SELECT name
FROM resources
WHERE status = 'active';

external_knowledge:
- 'read access' implies permission to view the resource without making modifications; 
- 'metadata version' refers to the version of the resource's metadata; 
- 'latest resource states' refers to the most recent version of each resource as determined by the created_at timestamp.

sql:
SELECT name, description
FROM graph_definitions
WHERE status = 'active';

SELECT resource_id, MAX(version) AS latest_version
FROM resource_versions
GROUP BY resource_id;

SELECT MAX(version) AS latest_version
FROM resource_versions
WHERE resource_id = 1;
